         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head><p>
               <supplied reason="lost">
                  <note>?In honour of</note> Emperor Caesar Trajan Hadrian Augustus</supplied>, <supplied reason="subaudible">son</supplied> of <supplied reason="lost">deified Trajan conqueror of Parthia, grandson</supplied> of deified Nerva, <supplied reason="lost">Chief Priest</supplied>, holding tribunician power for the seventh time, consul <supplied reason="lost">for the third</supplied>
               <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>Hadrian's 7th tribunician year was 10th December 122 - 9th December 123. For Hadrian's relations with Apollonia see
                    also IG II2 3306 <!--Link to # PH5579 -->  at Athens, dated (by the use of the title <foreign xml:lang="la">Olympius</foreign>) after
                    128/9, in which the Apolloniates describe him as <foreign xml:lang="grc">οἰκιστής</foreign>, presumably for help given in
                    the restoration of the city after the Jewish Revolt of AD 115. It may be that
                    the emperor's name here was in the nominative and that the text recorded a gift
                    to the city as in an inscription of the same date as this at Taucheira <!--PerhapsT.1?-->and in
                    several at Cyrene (e.g. <ref type="inscription">C24200</ref>).</p>
         </div>
         
